2 HOUSE BILL 899
1 WHEREAS, There are over 350,000 Muslim Marylanders who currently reside in
2 the State and, for generations, have contributed to enriching the artistic, business,
3 academic, and public service communities thereby significantly increasing the vibrancy of
4 Maryland; and
5 WHEREAS, There are over 250,000 Jewish Marylanders who currently reside in the
6 State and, for generations, have contributed to enriching the artistic, business, academic,
7 and public service communities thereby significantly increasing the vibrancy of Maryland;
8 now, therefore,
9 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
10 That Section(s) 7–501 through 7–503 and 7–504 through 7–507 of Article – General
11 Provisions of the Annotated Code of Maryland be renumbered to be Section(s) 7–502
12 through 7–504 and 7–506 through 7–509, respectively.
13 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That the Laws of Maryland read
14 as follows:
15 Article – General Provisions
16 7–501.
17 (A) THE GOVERNOR ANNUALLY SHALL PROCLAIM THE MONTH OF JANUARY
18 AS MUSLIM AMERICAN HERITAGE MONTH IN RECOGNITION OF THE
19 CONTRIBUTIONS THAT MUSLIM AMERICANS HAVE MADE TO THE STATE.
20 (B) THE PROCLAMATION SHALL URGE EDUCATIONAL AND CULTURAL
21 ORGANIZATIONS TO OBSERVE MUSLIM AMERICAN HERITAGE MONTH PROPERLY
22 WITH APPROPRIATE PROGRAMS, CEREMONIES, AND ACTIVITIES.
23 7–505.
24 (A) THE GOVERNOR ANNUALLY SHALL PROCLAIM THE MONTH OF MAY AS
25 JEWISH AMERICAN HERITAGE MONTH IN RECOGNITION OF THE CONTRIBUTIONS
26 THAT JEWISH AMERICANS HAVE MADE TO THE STATE.
27 (B) THE PROCLAMATION SHALL URGE EDUCATIONAL AND CULTURAL
28 ORGANIZATIONS TO OBSERVE JEWISH AMERICAN HERITAGE MONTH PROPERLY
29 WITH APPROPRIATE PROGRAMS, CEREMONIES, AND ACTIVITIES.
30 SECTION 3. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
31 October 1, 2025.

